build

public RpcResult build(User user,
                       long projectId,
                       String target)
Make a request to the Build Server to build a project. The Build Server will asynchronously post the results of the build via the ReceiveBuildServlet A later call will need to be made by the client in order to get those results.

Specified by:
build in class CommonProjectService
Parameters:
user - the User that owns the projectId.
projectId - project id to be built
target - build target (optional, implementation dependent)
Returns:
an RpcResult reflecting the call to the Build Server

getBuildResult

public RpcResult getBuildResult(User user,
                                long projectId,
                                String target)
Check if there are any build results available for the given user's project

Specified by:
getBuildResult in class CommonProjectService
Parameters:
user - the User that owns the projectId.
projectId - project id to be built
target - build target (optional, implementation dependent)
Returns:
an RpcResult reflecting the call to the Build Server. The following values may be in RpcResult.result: 0: Build is done and was successful 1: Build is done and was unsuccessful 2: Yail generation failed -1: Build is not yet done.
